Enum IStatement.StatementType

    public static enum IStatement.StatementType
extends java.lang.Enum<IStatement.StatementType>
    The types of statements we foresee. At this point we have: - ask - block - construct - describe - parentheses-block (in SPARQL it is valid to insert something between { and } without it preceded by 'where' or 'insert' or ... - select-block - simple statement (this is basicly just a string) - update-block (insert and delete) - where-block
